column5: We are considering a day trip to wawapus. Has anyone fished this lake? Is it stained or clear? Weedy, rocky? Good walleye population? Smallmouth? Worth the trip? Any info would be greatly appreciated.

If its the Wawapus lake in Dryden On,its tea stained.Its a chain of 5 lakes if i remember correctly.Not a very wide chain of lakes.There is a few rock piles that are hitable.Good fishing in the bays with cabbage weeds.Walleye,Pirch and Pike no Bass.
